article.headline: E. Illinois 78, Jacksonville St. 69
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Tyler Laser scored 22 points to lead Eastern Illinois to a 78-69 win over Jacksonville State on Saturday night. Laser shot 5-for-10 from the floor, including 3-for-5 from 3-point range. The Panthers (5-8, 2-1 Ohio Valley Conference) also received a boost from Billy Parrish and T.J. Marion, who scored 15 apiece. Romain Martin and Ousmane Cisse each scored 12. Jeremy Bynum led the Gamecocks (7-4, 1-1 Ohio Valley) with 15 points. Jonathan Toles finished with 14 points and six assists. DeAndre Bray contributed 11 assists. The Panthers shot 51 percent from the field (25-for-49), and 85.2 percent from the free-throw line (23-for-27). Jacksonville State shot 40 percent (24-for-60), and only 58.8 percent from the free-throw line (10-for-17). The Panthers outrebouded the Gamecocks 37-25.
